Class-name translation data
---------------------------

Steam re-hashes its compiled CSS class names on every release, which
breaks community themes that target old build hashes. The deckthemes
API publishes a JSON map of every observed class name across builds
keyed by stable identifiers. This plugin fetches that map at runtime
from `https://api.deckthemes.com/stable.json` (a public, CORS-open
endpoint) and applies it locally to rewrite stale selectors before
injecting them. The map is cached under
`~/.cache/steam-loader/theme-loader/` on the user's machine. It is not
bundled or redistributed.


Community theme directory
-------------------------

The community theme directory is fetched live at runtime from the
public deckthemes.com API endpoints
`https://api.deckthemes.com/themes` and
`https://api.deckthemes.com/themes/{id}`. Each entry carries factual
references — theme name, author, version, GitHub URL (when published),
and the upstream blob ids needed to fetch the download archive and
preview thumbnail. The selection is mechanical (every CSS-type theme,
ordered by download count) — there is no curation by us. The
response is cached under `~/.cache/steam-loader/theme-loader/` for
24h and is not bundled or redistributed.


Theme thumbnails
----------------

Theme preview thumbnails are not bundled. The directory carries a
`thumbnailUrl` field pointing at the upstream deckthemes CDN; the
user's CEF webview loads each image directly the same way any browser
viewing deckthemes.com does. Thumbnails remain owned by the theme
authors who uploaded them; this plugin neither caches nor re-hosts
them.


Installed themes
----------------

Themes installed through this plugin are downloaded from
deckthemes.com or GitHub at the user's request, into
`~/.local/share/steam-loader/css-themes/{themeId}/`. Each theme
remains governed by its own upstream license. When an upstream
LICENSE/COPYING file is present in the source archive, this plugin
preserves it on install and exposes it in the UI via a per-theme
`theme-meta.json` sidecar. Themes without a declared license are
surfaced in the UI as "License: not declared".
